A.9 — Phase A integrated smoke E2E. Closed 2026-05-13.

Run history:
  d9a16040-… (run 1) — caught real bug: worker IAM had no s3:PutObject on artifacts bucket. Fixed via BasicsWorkerTaskRoleArtifactsPolicy + redeploy.
  86486ff5-… (run 2) — caught real bug: opencode-plugin built per-tool-call WorkerToolContext without injecting quotaStore. Fixed by wiring PgQuotaStore in the plugin + redeploy.
  20f46f85-… (run 3) — caught real bug: PgQuotaStore shared the worker's max:1/idle_timeout:5 pg connection; dropped under concurrency with "write CONNECTION_ENDED". Fixed by giving quotaStore its own dedicated pool (max:2/idle_timeout:60).
  31e06d13-… (run 4) — primary path green (attach_artifact + send_email-with-attachment + send_sms). Screenshot subtest stalled because the prompt asked the model to round-trip the base64 PNG through attach_artifact's payload — but the OC adapter strips b64 from kind:image results, so the bytes were never reachable. Caught real architecture bug: screenshot wasn't S3-persistable, only b64-visible to (now stripped from) the model.
  9d7ffda7-… (run 5, image v4) — FULL SUCCESS in 95s after screenshot tool was extended to PUT to s3://basics-runtime-artifacts-production/workspaces/.../runs/.../screenshots/<name>.png and return {s3Key, signedUrl, byteLength, mimeType}. Plus formatForOpencode surfaces those fields as JSON output. 4 output_dispatched events: artifact, email (with test.json attached), sms, email (with example.png attached). Both emails confirmed received by operator (dmrknife@gmail.com).
  ee40a452-… (run 6, image v4) — MMS-with-screenshot confirmation. screenshot → send_sms with mediaUrl = screenshot.signedUrl → operator received the example.com screenshot as MMS at +19722144223. Also send_email cross-check landed in dmrknife@gmail.com. Completed in 167s.

Plan-spec verify items (per docs/AUTOMATIONS-PLAN.md §A.9):
  [✓] 3 output_dispatched events with correct channels — runs 5 + 6 collectively logged artifact, email (×3), sms (×2) rows in cloud_activity.
  [✓] Operator inbox shows the email — confirmed by operator (received Phase A smoke + screenshot emails).
  [✓] Operator phone shows the SMS — confirmed by operator (received both plain SMS and the MMS with screenshot).
  [✓] Signed URL from attach_artifact resolves to the JSON content — presign + curl returned 200 with matching body (78 bytes).
  [✓] SELECT * FROM cloud_activity WHERE run_id = … AND activity_type = 'output_dispatched' returns ≥3 rows for runs 5 and 6.
  [✓] Screenshot → S3 → email path (operator-requested extension) — green via the new screenshot tool persistence layer.
  [✓] Screenshot → S3 → MMS path (operator-requested extension) — green; Sendblue mediaUrl renders the PNG inline on iMessage.

Real bugs caught by live agent runs (none would have been caught by unit tests):
  1. Missing worker IAM s3:PutObject on artifacts bucket.
  2. opencode-plugin per-tool-call WorkerToolContext didn't inject quotaStore.
  3. PgQuotaStore was given the worker's aggressively-idle-timed shared pg connection.
  4. screenshot tool's b64 was always stripped by the OC adapter — there was no S3-persisted handle the agent could pass to other tools.

Tool-surface changes from A.9:
  - shared/src/tools/define.ts: ToolResult kind:image variant gained optional s3Key, signedUrl, byteLength.
  - worker/src/tools/screenshot.ts: writes PNG to s3://{ARTIFACTS_S3_BUCKET}/workspaces/<ws>/runs/<run>/screenshots/<name>.png by default; 7-day signedUrl; optional `name` param for stable filenames. Falls back to b64-only if S3 fails.
  - worker/src/opencode-plugin/index.ts: formatForOpencode now surfaces image s3Key + signedUrl + byteLength + mimeType as JSON for the model when present.
  - 5 worker tests updated (registry size 32 → 35). Full suite 261/261.

